{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-04-06T00:43:53.885Z","tool_name":"run_shell_command","tool_id":"run_shell_command_1775436233885_0","parameters":{"description":"Create README files for papers and datasets.","command":"cat > papers/README.md << 'EOF'\n# Downloaded Papers\n\n1. [The Linear Representation Hypothesis and the Geometry of Large Language Models](park2023_linear_representation_hypothesis.pdf) (2023)\n   - Authors: Kiho Park, Yo Joong Choe, Victor Veitch\n   - Key: Foundational formalization of LRH using causal inner products.\n\n2. [The Geometries of Truth Are Orthogonal Across Tasks](azizian2025_geometries_of_truth_orthogonal.pdf) (2025)\n   - Authors: Waiss Azizian et al.\n   - Key: Demonstrates task-specific truth directions and failure to generalize.\n\n3. [Algorithmic Primitives and Compositional Geometry of Reasoning](lippl2025_algorithmic_primitives.pdf) (2025)\n   - Authors: Samuel Lippl et al.\n   - Key: Shows that structural/algorithmic directions are more compositional.\n\n4. [Stop Probing, Start Coding: Why Linear Probes and SAEs Fail at Compositional Generalisation](stop_probing_start_coding_2026.pdf) (2026)\n   - Authors: Vitoria Barin Pacela et al.\n   - Key: Challenges linear accessibility under superposition and compositional shifts.\n\n5. [PolySAE: Modeling Feature Interactions in Sparse Autoencoders via Polynomial Decoding](polysae2026_compositional_sae.pdf) (2026)\n   - Authors: Panagiotis Koromilas et al.\n   - Key: Highlights the need for non-linear multiplicative terms for semantic composition.\n\n6. [The Geometry of Categorical and Hierarchical Concepts in LLMs](park2024_geometry_categorical_hierarchical.pdf) (2024)\n   - Authors: Kiho Park et al.\n   - Key: Extends LRH to polytopes and hierarchical orthogonality.\n\n7. [The Geometry of Truth: Emergent Linear Structure in LLMs](marks2023_geometry_of_truth.pdf) (2023)\n   - Authors: Samuel Marks, Max Tegmark\n   - Key: Seminal paper on linear truth representations.\n\n8. [Comp. Gen. Requires Linear, Orthogonal Representations in Vision](compositional_generalization_linear_orthogonal_2026.pdf) (2026)\n   - Authors: Koromilas et al.\n   - Key: Explores similar themes in vision models.\nEOF\n\ncat > datasets/README.md << 'EOF'\n# Downloaded Datasets\n\n## Dataset 1: TruthfulQA\n- **Source**: HuggingFace `truthfulqa/truthful_qa`\n- **Location**: `datasets/truthful_qa.csv`\n- **Task**: Evaluate truthfulness and hallucination.\n\n## Dataset 2: TriviaQA (Sample)\n- **Source**: HuggingFace `trivia_qa`\n- **Location**: `datasets/trivia_qa_sample.csv`\n- **Task**: Used for extracting truth directions (correct vs. incorrect fact recall).\n\n## Dataset 3: Word Pairs (Semantic)\n- **Source**: `code/park_geometry/word_pairs/`\n- **Task**: Provides directions for gender, language, countries, etc.\n\n## Dataset 4: Logical Transformations\n- **Source**: `code/truthfulness_probes/data/`\n- **Task**: Specifically negation, conjunction, and disjunction pairs for truth.\n\n## Dataset 5: WordNet Hierarchy\n- **Source**: `code/park_categorical/data/`\n- **Task**: 900+ concepts with hierarchical relationships.\n\n## .gitignore for Datasets\nA `.gitignore` has been created to exclude large data files from git while keeping documentation.\nEOF\n\ncat > datasets/.gitignore << 'EOF'\n*\n!.gitignore\n!README.md\n!**/*.md\n!**/samples/\n!**/*.csv\nEOF\n"}}
